00:02:01.010 --> 00:02:03.260
of disciplines and cultures.

00:02:03.260 --> 00:02:06.560
It offers a forum to
foster thoughtful dialogue,

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:08.670
and an opportunity to be inspired

00:02:08.670 --> 00:02:12.820
by outstanding and
accomplished women leaders.

00:02:12.820 --> 00:02:16.170
Today's lecturer, as you will hear,

00:02:16.170 --> 00:02:17.590
certainly fits this mold.

00:02:17.590 --> 00:02:20.180
Professor Laura Tyson is remarkable

00:02:20.180 --> 00:02:23.030
for her accomplishments and impact,

00:02:23.030 --> 00:02:26.793
not just in academia, but
also in public service.

00:02:27.740 --> 00:02:31.470
The inaugural lecture
in the HarvEst Series

00:02:31.470 --> 00:02:36.470
was presented by Harriet
Fulbright in October of 2013.

00:02:36.570 --> 00:02:38.460
And like our event today,

00:02:38.460 --> 00:02:41.740
was convened here at International House.

00:02:41.740 --> 00:02:43.900
This is the perfect setting for dialogue

00:02:43.900 --> 00:02:47.170
centered on shaping a world
of greater understanding,

00:02:47.170 --> 00:02:50.023
and where diversity of
perspective is welcome.

00:02:50.910 --> 00:02:53.100
But also, International House is a place

00:02:53.100 --> 00:02:56.700
where individuals are
encouraged to dream big

00:02:56.700 --> 00:02:59.533
and see that they can
truly change the world.

00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:03.500
The HarvEst name originates from combining

00:03:03.500 --> 00:03:06.921
the first names of our
lecture benefactors.

00:03:06.921 --> 00:03:11.550
UC Berkeley alumni couple,
Harvey Lee, of '88,

00:03:11.550 --> 00:03:15.460
and Esther Ma, '87, both of Hong Kong.

00:03:15.460 --> 00:03:18.380
I'm delighted to say
that Esther and Harvey

00:03:18.380 --> 00:03:20.220
are here today with us,

00:03:20.220 --> 00:03:23.370
along with several of
their family members.

00:03:23.370 --> 00:03:24.770
So if you get a chance,

00:03:24.770 --> 00:03:27.623
do give them a warm
welcome back to Berkeley.

00:03:28.488 --> 00:03:30.738
(applause)

