01:17:33.810 --> 01:17:35.350
Many Americans, many people in the world

01:17:35.350 --> 01:17:37.100
are very unaware of such things,

01:17:37.100 --> 01:17:38.870
but clearly the events and steps taken

01:17:38.870 --> 01:17:42.330
by Merkel and Hollande
indicates such a situation.

01:17:42.330 --> 01:17:43.163
Now the other side of it,

01:17:43.163 --> 01:17:46.930
and this is the economic
question, is Greece,

01:17:46.930 --> 01:17:48.030
and what Greece indicates.

01:17:48.030 --> 01:17:49.693
Because it's a very big question,

01:17:50.650 --> 01:17:52.100
and Greece has an option.

01:17:52.100 --> 01:17:54.440
Where I'm not sure the
European Union does.

01:17:54.440 --> 01:17:56.800
There are nations now known as the BRICS,

01:17:56.800 --> 01:18:01.060
Russia, China, India,
Brazil, South Africa,

01:18:01.060 --> 01:18:04.350
nations like Egypt or Argentina
which are joining them,

01:18:04.350 --> 01:18:08.000
with incredible economic
growth commitments.

01:18:08.000 --> 01:18:10.320
Engineering, science, food production.

01:18:10.320 --> 01:18:11.973
Just remarkable process.

01:18:14.150 --> 01:18:15.940
So I'd like to know, we have an initiative

01:18:15.940 --> 01:18:19.470
for the United States to join
in that process, the BRICS,

01:18:19.470 --> 01:18:20.880
and I'd like to know if you would

01:18:20.880 --> 01:18:22.050
support something like that,

01:18:22.050 --> 01:18:25.270
and what you generally think
in this political context

01:18:25.270 --> 01:18:27.330
of this economic question,

01:18:27.330 --> 01:18:29.380
which does seem to be
a bit of an east, west,

01:18:29.380 --> 01:18:32.530
or just a divide of two
systems in the world today.

01:18:32.530 --> 01:18:35.740
I don't think the question's
relevant to this talk,

01:18:35.740 --> 01:18:36.990
but I have thought a lot.

01:18:36.990 --> 01:18:38.840
I mean if you're talking about BRICS,

01:18:40.750 --> 01:18:43.420
Brazil, Russia, is that
what you mean by BRICS?

01:18:43.420 --> 01:18:47.560
So the truth is, and it is relevant

01:18:47.560 --> 01:18:49.860
to this talk in one respect,

01:18:49.860 --> 01:18:54.860
there is an inexorable
and significant shift

01:18:54.890 --> 01:18:56.800
in the weight of the global economy,

01:18:56.800 --> 01:19:00.950
away from the developed
countries towards the BRICS,

01:19:00.950 --> 01:19:02.900
towards the emerging market economies.

01:19:02.900 --> 01:19:07.030
The two major economies that
drive global growth today

01:19:07.030 --> 01:19:08.830
are the US and China.

01:19:08.830 --> 01:19:12.380
China is growing, even with
a significant slow down,

01:19:12.380 --> 01:19:14.960
twice as fast as the US.

01:19:14.960 --> 01:19:16.980
China does, actually, quite a good job,

01:19:16.980 --> 01:19:18.810
and it would be interesting to hear

01:19:18.810 --> 01:19:22.750
Esther and Harvey talk about
this, on gender issues,

01:19:22.750 --> 01:19:27.750
on mobilizing their
talented female workforce,

01:19:28.210 --> 01:19:32.140
and on educating their female workforce.

01:19:32.140 --> 01:19:35.310
But there clearly is this shift going on

01:19:35.310 --> 01:19:40.310
in the world economy,
and different society,

01:19:40.810 --> 01:19:42.950
so what I was trying to say by this

01:19:42.950 --> 01:19:47.480
is that you can see that across society,

01:19:47.480 --> 01:19:48.880
at different levels of development,

01:19:48.880 --> 01:19:51.220
even ones that have been committed to

01:19:51.220 --> 01:19:53.580
gender parity for a very long time,

01:19:53.580 --> 01:19:55.970
and have it deeply embedded
in their cultural norms,

01:19:55.970 --> 01:19:59.130
and deeply embedded in their
political institutions,

01:19:59.130 --> 01:20:03.170
have a ways to go, and those
would be the Nordic countries.

01:20:03.170 --> 01:20:04.910
A very interesting
thing going on right now

01:20:04.910 --> 01:20:08.480
