01:20:34.637 --> 01:20:37.047
"with business leaders in our society

01:20:37.047 --> 01:20:42.047
"to improve our performance on
the gender parity measures."

01:20:42.610 --> 01:20:44.120
So what were these countries?

01:20:44.120 --> 01:20:46.070
One was Turkey.

01:20:46.070 --> 01:20:47.880
One was Korea.

01:20:47.880 --> 01:20:50.130
One is India.

01:20:50.130 --> 01:20:53.040
And one is Mexico.

01:20:53.040 --> 01:20:54.927
So these are countries that
just came forward and said,

01:20:54.927 --> 01:20:58.127
"You know, we really
think we can do better.

01:20:58.127 --> 01:20:59.597
"We see the case here,

01:20:59.597 --> 01:21:02.187
"we see that there's
economic benefit to this.

01:21:02.187 --> 01:21:04.387
"We see that we have very talented women

01:21:04.387 --> 01:21:05.677
"that we're not mobilizing enough.

01:21:05.677 --> 01:21:07.580
"Let us work on this together."

01:21:07.580 --> 01:21:10.230
So I think, let's say emerging markets

01:21:10.230 --> 01:21:11.630
are becoming more and more important,

01:21:11.630 --> 01:21:14.390
and a number of the big ones now

01:21:14.390 --> 01:21:17.210
are focused on this issue.

01:21:17.210 --> 01:21:20.920
And that's how I will
relate to the question,

01:21:20.920 --> 01:21:23.695
because it's hard for
me to draw another link.

